[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/feos 
		"feos
	]a
	": Claiming for judging.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/feos 
		"feos
	]a
	": Great work as always, indeed the only tricky part was the branching. These days we're as open to extra Alternative/Moons branches as we've ever been, so my initial instinct would be to just label the current publication(s) and accept this one to Standard.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Turns out it's impossible to come up with an accurate label that would describe what 
	(__wikiLink|href=/1063M|implicitdisplaytext=1063M)
	" actually aims for instead of fastest completion. It has 
	[b 
		"some
	]b
	" in-bounds decisions - it avoids some clips but not all of them, and it could have avoided more if Air 1 was used, since it offers infinite jumps. It has 
	[b 
		"some
	]b
	" playaround, but it also sometimes just uses a slower route without it being any more entertaining.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"How do we know it's not super entertaining either? When it was initially judged, the preference of this movie over 
	(__wikiLink|href=/434M|implicitdisplaytext=434M)
	" was marginal, and that is reflected in the judgment note. And even then, once 
	(__wikiLink|href=/4347S|implicitdisplaytext=4347S)
	" appeared, it was considered to be superior than mushroom's run and obsoleted it, since back then we aimed for the most entertainment and difference with hacks.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"All in all, if 
	(__wikiLink|href=/1828S|implicitdisplaytext=1828S)
	" was submitted today, it would not have met the 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Alt requirements|href=/MovieRules#Alternative)
	", and would have been rejected, as having a goal that's too vague, not very different, and not very entertaining.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Accepting this movie over 
	(__wikiLink|href=/1063M|implicitdisplaytext=1063M)
	".
	$LF
]div
